Chairman Dan Rostenkowski of thetax-writing House Ways and Means Committee said today PresidentReagan must reconsider his consistent opposition to any taxincreases.    The Illinois Democrat, asked on a television interview (onNBC-Today) about the possibility of tax hikes, said, "I thinkthe president is going to have to reconsider."    He added, "I just hope there's enough vision in thisadministration to recognize that our deficits are intolerableand the only way we're going to do it is by raising revenues." Reuter&#3;